        public void createIndex(java.lang.String strColName)
                 throws DBAppException,
                        java.io.FileNotFoundException,
                        java.io.IOException,
                        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
        create index on specified column name by creating BPTree on that column and inserting in it.
        Parameters:
        strColName - The name of the column which index is created on
        Throws:
        DBAppException - If columns, foreign keys or the primary key are not valid
        java.io.FileNotFoundException - If an error occurred in the stored table file
        java.io.IOException - If an I/O error occurred
        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException - If an error occurred in the stored table pages format
